<subSubSection pageId="133" pageNumber="704" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="133.[2095,2680,2675,3097]" pageId="133" pageNumber="704">
Closely related to the Japanese Serow (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[2109,2244,2789,2822]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Capricornis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="133" pageNumber="704" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crispus">C. crispus</taxonomicName>
) but molecular genetic data indicate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1862" box="[2224,2373,2828,2861]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Capricornus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="133" pageNumber="704" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="swinhoei">C. swinhoei</taxonomicName>
1s a separate species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
